%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20wife%20and%20I%20blended%20our%20last%20names.%20We%20wanted%20to%20share%20a%20last%20name%20that%20was%20uniquely%20ours.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20during%20wedding%20day%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b2a9f6f4b446f3be9d1849%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(right)%20and%20his%20wife%20chose%20to%20blend%20their%20last%20names%20to%20create%20something%20that%20was%20more%20them%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Storytellers%20Wedding%20Co.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20didn't%20know%20that%20blending%20your%20last%20names%20was%20already%20a%20trend%20when%20we%20did%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20share%20a%20last%20name%20instead%20of%20one%20or%20the%20other%20taking%20a%20new%20name.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20had%20the%20new%20last%20name%20engraved%20in%20the%20inside%20of%20our%20rings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20decided%20to%20do%20it%2C%20my%20now-wife%20and%20I%20didn't%20know%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funique-baby-names-from-1975-to-2016-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ename%20blending%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20growing%20trend%2C%20but%20we%20knew%20it%20was%20right%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20couple%2C%20we've%20always%20been%20somewhat%20unconventional%3B%20we%20moved%20in%20together%20after%20two%20weeks%20of%20dating%2C%20had%20a%20four-year-%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-prefer-longer-engagements-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20engagement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20got%20married%20on%20our%2010th%20anniversary%20%E2%80%94%20for%20it%20to%20feel%20like%20%3Cem%3Eus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20our%20marriage%20had%20to%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20blended%20our%20last%20names%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EName%20blending%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20the%20practice%20of%20creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-didnt-change-my-last-name-after-marriage-how-its-going%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20last%20name%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20the%20letters%20of%20each%20partner's%20maiden%20name.%20With%20the%20institute%20of%20marriage%20becoming%20more%20flexible%2C%20it's%20becoming%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20what%20to%20do%20with%20our%20last%20names%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-took-wife-last-name-married-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditional%20route%3C%2Fa%3E%20didn't%20feel%20right%20to%20us%2C%20but%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20share%20a%20last%20name.%20A%20lot%20of%20couples%20resolve%20this%20by%20hyphenating%2C%20but%20our%20names%20just%20don't%20sound%20good%20hyphenated%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20name%20was%20Egan%2C%20and%20my%20wife's%20last%20name%20was%20Michell%2C%20which%20would%20have%20made%20us%20either%20The%20Michell-Egans%20or%20The%20Egan-Michells%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eneither%20of%20these%20sounded%20good%20to%20us.%20We%20puzzled%20on%20this%20for%20a%20while%20until%20my%20wife%20suggested%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20we%20just%20create%20our%20own%20name%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20joked%20about%20having%20a%20celebrity%20couple%20portmanteau%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fangelina-jolie-and-brad-pitt-relationship-history-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrangelina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bennifer%2C%20or%20TomKat.%20Unfortunately%20for%20us%2C%20this%20would%20give%20us%20the%20choice%20between%20being%20The%20Egchells%20or%20The%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EMichegans.%20We%20realized%20that%20we%20needed%20to%20get%20creative%2C%20so%20we%20whipped%20out%20the%20Scrabble%20board%20and%20got%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20families%20loved%20the%20idea%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20a%20long%20engagement%20and%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20discuss%20this.%20After%20weeding%20out%20all%20of%20the%20'teasable'%20names%2C%20we'd%20narrowed%20it%20down%20to%20five%20candidates%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGailen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EMagellan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EGallen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ENeilan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EHaigen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20at%20last%2C%20we%20arrived%20at%20what%20would%20be%20our%20new%20name%3A%20Haigen.%20We%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20good%2C%20strong-sounding%20name.%20It%20honored%20my%20Celtic%20roots%20(a%20selling%20point%20for%20my%20Dad%2C%20who%20I%20hadn't%20mustered%20the%20courage%20to%20tell%20yet)%2C%20and%20it%20rolled%20off%20the%20tongue%20nicely%20with%20both%20of%20our%20first%20names%3A%20Selena%20%26amp%3B%20William%20Haigen%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221122%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22List%20of%20names%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b2aa83f4b446f3be9d187d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22841%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThey%20had%20a%20shortlist%20of%20five%20names%20that%20they%20liked%20before%20they%20picked%20the%20final%20mix%20of%20names%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20deciding%2C%20we%20had%20the%20name%20engraved%20on%20the%20inside%20our%20rings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20family%20and%20friends%20loved%20the%20idea%2C%20but%20we%20noticed%20a%20general%20trend%3A%20The%20older%20the%20person%20was%2C%20the%20longer%20it%20took%20for%20them%20to%20process.%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Millenials%20immediately%20liked%20the%20idea%2C%20Gen%20X%20liked%20it%20after%20a%20few%20seconds%2C%20and%20Baby%20Boomers%20had%20to%20sleep%20on%20it.%20What%20we%20didn't%20share%20was%20the%20name%20itself.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EOur%20secrecy%20prompted%20a%20lot%20of%20wild%20guesses%20from%20friends%20and%20family.%20These%20ranged%20from%20Legen%20%3Cem%3E(%3C%2Fem%3Esounds%20like%20%26quot%3Blegend%26quot%3B)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20Megan%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20our%20favourite%2C%20Hellnag%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3EOn%20the%20big%20day%2C%20we%20proudly%20unveiled%20the%20name%20to%20our%20friends%20and%20family%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ceremony%20to%20a%20round%20of%20applause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20in%20a%20name.%20A%20name%20carries%20our%20sense%20of%20identity%2C%20and%20so%20of%20course%2C%20there's%20often%20a%20resistance%20to%20letting%20it%20go.%20But%20with%20our%20blended%20name%2C%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20we've%20let%20our%20names%20go.%20The%20pieces%20of%20our%20names%20are%20still%20there%3B%20they've%20just%20been%20rearranged%20and%20combined%20with%20each%20other's.%20For%20us%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20the%20perfect%20symbol%20of%20what%20we%20want%20for%20our%20marriage%3A%20to%20merge%20with%20another%20half%20while%20still%20keeping%20our%20own%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20my%20wife's%20identity%20changing%20into%20mine%20or%20our%20identities%20sitting%20alongside%20each%20other's%2C%20connected%20only%20by%20a%20hyphen%2C%20they're%20blended%20into%20something%20new%20that%20we%20created%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblended-last-names-after-marriage-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706440981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b2aa3ef4b446f3be9d185c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblended-last-names-after-marriage-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20couple%20blended%20their%20last%20names%20instead%20of%20one%20spouse%20taking%20the%20other's%20so%20they%20could%20share%20something%20unique.%20Their%20families%20were%20supportive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(William%20Egan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblended-last-names-after-marriage-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gig%20driving%20was%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20for%20many%20people%20with%20disabilities%20%E2%80%94%20but%20for%20some%2C%20it's%20a%20dead%20end.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20hand%20holding%20a%20phone%20in%20a%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b3e5b06c8f0a134f7a417e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmericans%20with%20disabilities%20are%20overrepresented%20in%20gig%20work%2C%20where%20they%20have%20more%20flexibility.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20drivers%20said%20driving%20for%20companies%2C%20including%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%2C%20is%20their%20only%20option.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20can't%20find%20other%20accommodating%20jobs%20and%20that%20gig%20work%20is%20a%20dead%20end.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20has%20to%20tell%20all%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-hours-uber-lyft-drivers-work-taxi-competitive-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20riders%20that%20he%20can't%20help%20them%20with%20their%20luggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriving-for-uber-lyft-disability-stock-portland-cost-of-living-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E56-year-old%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20recently%20injured%20his%20arm%20helping%20a%20passenger%20with%20a%20heavy%20bag.%20Robert%20was%20born%20with%20an%20arteriovenous%20malformation%2C%20a%20tangle%20of%20blood%20vessels%20in%20his%20brain.%20The%20former%20construction%20worker%20had%20a%20stroke%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20after%20which%20he%20had%20multiple%20brain%20surgeries%2C%20resulting%20in%20paralysis%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20his%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20gig%20driving%20was%20one%20of%20his%20only%20options%20to%20supplement%20his%20disability%20benefits.%20He%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-retirement-social-security-taxes-gig-economy-drivers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriving%20for%20Lyft%20and%20Uber%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017%20%E2%80%94%20a%20temporary%20way%20to%20pull%20in%20enough%20to%20live%20comfortably%2C%20he%20thought%20at%20the%20time.%20He%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20make%20driving%20work%20for%20him%2C%20though%20what%20used%20to%20be%20a%20three-day-a-week%20job%20has%20become%20a%20nearly%20everyday%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20get%20to%20thinking%20there's%20got%20to%20be%20something%20I%20can%20do%20besides%20this%2C%20but%20there's%20really%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20any%20options%2C%20and%20almost%20all%20jobs%20require%20you%20to%20stand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20tries%20to%20make%20at%20least%20%24100%20daily%20and%20is%20often%20up%20at%205%3A30%20a.m.%20to%20get%20more%20profitable%20rides.%20Since%20he%20can%20only%20work%20a%20set%20number%20of%20hours%20while%20keeping%20his%20disability%20benefits%2C%20he%20said%20he's%20struggled%20to%20pay%20his%20bills%20because%2C%20on%20some%20slow%20days%2C%20he%20only%20makes%20%2415%20an%20hour%20before%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20has%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20keep%20driving%20and%20maximizing%20tips.%20He%20said%20he's%20received%20poor%20ratings%20from%20passengers%20who%20misunderstood%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20disregarded%20%E2%80%94%20his%20disabilities.%20Even%20though%20he%20temporarily%20quit%20driving%20to%20try%20other%20jobs%2C%20nothing%20else%20has%20stuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20is%20one%20of%20many%20disabled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteacher-quit-to-become-full-time-uber-lyft-driver-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20say%20they%20have%20no%20other%20options%20to%20make%20a%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDisabled%20gig%20workers%20can%20be%20forced%20to%20rely%20on%20gig%20work%20for%20income%20because%20of%20issues%20with%20exclusion%20and%20discrimination%20in%20traditional%20workplaces%2C%26quot%3B%20Shruti%20Sannon%2C%20a%20technology-policy%20program%20director%20at%20the%20ACLU%20who%20authored%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrutisannon.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2FSannon-Cosley-CSCW2022-Toward-a-More-Inclusive-Gig-Economy-Risks-and-Opportunities-for-Workers-with-Disabilities.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%20on%20disabled%20gig%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%20Sannon%20said%20that%20while%20disabled%20workers%20%26quot%3Bcan%20earn%20much-needed%20income%20via%20these%20platforms%2C%20they%20also%20have%20to%20navigate%20a%20range%20of%20complicated%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20statements%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20outlined%20their%20commitments%20to%20supporting%20disabled%20drivers%20through%20accessibility%20and%20antidiscrimination%20policies%20and%20resources%20for%20various%20physical%20and%20mental%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLyft%20is%20committed%20to%20maintaining%20an%20inclusive%20and%20welcoming%20community%20and%20strongly%20condemns%20discrimination%20of%20any%20kind%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Lyft%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BDrivers%20should%20contact%20our%20support%20teams%20concerning%20potentially%20discriminatory%20reviews%20or%20trends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUber%20provides%20a%20platform%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%20to%20achieve%20earning%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAnyone%20who%20is%20legally%20able%20to%20drive%20can%20apply%20to%20drive%20with%20Uber.%20Vehicle%20modifications%20such%20as%20hand%20controls%20and%20pedal%20extensions%20are%20adaptive%20options%20that%20drivers%20use.%20Uber%20policy%20does%20not%20require%20drivers%20to%20help%20passengers%20with%20their%20luggage.%20Except%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fau%2Fen%2Fride%2Fassist%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20Assist%20%3C%2Fa%3Erides%2C%20drivers%20are%20not%20expected%20to%20help%20passengers%20in%20and%20out%20of%20vehicles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20spoke%20with%2012%20disabled%20ride-hailing%20drivers%20about%20their%20experiences%20with%20driving%20as%20their%20main%20source%20of%20income.%20All%20said%20driving%20has%20become%20harder%20over%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20and%20most%20said%20they're%20lost%20on%20what%20to%20do%20next%20because%20driving%20is%20among%20their%20only%20job%20options.%20Though%20their%20last%20names%20are%20known%20to%20BI%2C%20most%20asked%20to%20use%20just%20their%20first%20names%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20and%20more%20disabled%20people%20are%20turning%20to%20driving%20for%20flexible%20work%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20mixed%20bag%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20disabled%20drivers%20have%20had%20positive%20experiences%20driving%20for%20ride-hailing%20companies%2C%20noting%20that%20driving%20has%20helped%20them%20supplement%20their%20income%2C%20overcome%20loneliness%2C%20and%20stay%20busy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrivers%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-eats-driver-how-to-get-good-tips-stay-safe-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOmar%20Ford%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2047-year-old%20Uber%20Eats%20and%20DoorDash%20driver%20in%20South%20Florida%20who%20receives%20disability%20benefits%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20driving%20helps%20supplement%20his%20pension%20and%20benefits%20and%20allows%20him%20to%20overcome%20social%20anxiety%20and%20talk%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-help-loneliness-gig-economy-work-las-vegas-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJason%20McConahy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2048-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-lyft-drivers-make-per-ride-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epart-time%20Lyft%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20suffered%20a%20serious%20back%20injury%20over%20two%20decades%20ago%20and%20has%20collected%20disability%20benefits%20and%20cared%20for%20his%20kid%20for%20years.%20He%20started%20driving%20in%202016%20and%20said%20that%20while%20his%20income%20is%20sometimes%20inconsistent%2C%20he%20earned%20over%20%243%2C000%20across%20265%20trips%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20biggest%20benefit%20to%20driving%20with%20a%20disability%20is%20the%20opportunity%20to%20socialize%20with%20riders.%20Though%20he%20doesn't%20see%20gig%20driving%20as%20feasible%20for%20him%20full-time%2C%20it's%20given%20him%20peace%20of%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegardless%20of%20the%20type%20of%20passengers%2C%20it's%20human%20interaction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20previously%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bdriving%20for%20Lyft%20provides%20me%20with%20much-needed%20and%20appreciated%20social%20interactions%20outside%20my%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20other%20drivers%20told%20BI%20that%20their%20experiences%20have%20not%20been%20so%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESannon%20said%20many%20disabled%20Americans%20look%20to%20gig%20work%20to%20set%20their%20schedules%20around%20unpredictable%20medical%20appointments%20and%20symptoms.%20But%20she%20said%20disabled%20Americans%20face%20considerable%20hiring%20discrimination%2C%20meaning%20they%20often%20settle%20for%20%26quot%3Blow-paid%20and%20challenging%26quot%3B%20gig%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20gig%20platforms%2C%20and%20the%20tasks%20they%20offer%2C%20aren't%20designed%20with%20disability%20in%20mind.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20workers%20can%20encounter%20accessibility%20issues%20while%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Sannon%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20they%20can%20be%20entirely%20cut%20off%20from%20tasks%20that%20pay%20well%2C%20or%20they%20may%20expend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20effort%20on%20a%20task%20only%20to%20find%20out%20at%20the%20end%20that%20they%20can't%20complete%20it%20because%20of%20an%20accessibility%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESannon%20found%20that%20passengers%20often%20rated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-rideshare-gig-economy-worker-arizona-virginia-pandemic-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20mobility%20impairments%20poorly%20when%20they%20didn't%20help%20passengers%20with%20luggage.%20Ride-hailing%20platforms%20sometimes%20remove%20drivers%20with%20low%20ratings%20from%20the%20platforms%2C%20and%20some%20drivers%20told%20Sannon%20they%20didn't%20receive%20much%20long-term%20assistance%20from%20these%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20and%20Lyft%20told%20BI%20they%20protect%20drivers%20and%20riders%20from%20discrimination%20based%20on%20physical%20or%20mental%20disability.%20An%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20drivers%20nationwide%20earned%20on%20average%20%2435%20per%20utilized%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20the%20period%20between%20a%20driver%20accepting%20a%20ride%20and%20completing%20a%20trip%20%E2%80%94%20with%20bonuses%20and%20tips%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20apps%2C%20drivers%20can%20use%20accessibility%20features%20such%20as%20text%20instead%20of%20calls%20or%20screen%20flashes%20instead%20of%20auditory%20cues.%20They%20can%20also%20alert%20passengers%20if%20they%20are%20deaf%20or%20hard%20of%20hearing.%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20welcome%20service%20animals%20to%20ride%20with%20drivers%20and%20have%20policies%20and%20protections%20for%20drivers%20who%20use%20wheelchairs.%20Both%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20said%20they%20actively%20respond%20to%20allegations%20that%20a%20passenger%20gave%20a%20driver%20a%20low%20rating%20for%20any%20discriminatory%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Kruse%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Rutgers%20University%20School%20of%20Management%20and%20Labor%20Relations%2C%20and%20Lisa%20Schur%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20labor%20studies%20and%20employment%20relations%20at%20Rutgers%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20disabled%20workers%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they're%20doing%20this%20type%20of%20contingent%20work%20since%20they%20couldn't%20secure%20traditional%20full-time%20roles.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7610233%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20does%20not%20protect%20gig%20workers%2C%20meaning%20they're%20not%20always%20provided%20with%20reasonable%20accommodations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20sizable%20number%20of%20people%20in%20non-standard%20work%20arrangements%20said%20this%20is%20the%20only%20type%20of%20job%20they%20could%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20Schur%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20study%20analyzing%202017%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20of%2047%2C851%20people%2C%20Kruse%20and%20Schur%20found%20that%2021.5%25%20of%20responding%20employed%20people%20with%20disabilities%20were%20in%20contingent%20work%20as%20of%202017%2C%20compared%20to%2014.3%25%20of%20people%20without%20disabilities.%20Contingent%20workers%20with%20disabilities%20also%20face%20a%20pay%20gap%20and%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20health%20insurance%2C%20a%20pension%20plan%2C%20or%20union%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20they%20found%20employment%20of%20disabled%20people%20has%20been%20increasing%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20particularly%20in%20teleworking%20jobs.%20Both%20said%20increased%20employment%20protections%20for%20contingent%20workers%20could%20be%20a%20key%20to%20making%20gig%20work%20more%20equitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOftentimes%2C%20employers%20are%20reluctant%20to%20make%20accommodations%20in%20general%20but%20especially%20for%20people%20who%20may%20not%20be%20around%20for%20a%20while%2C%20and%20we%20find%20some%20evidence%20that%20contingent%20workers%20with%20disabilities%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20unmet%20accommodation%20means%2C%26quot%3B%20Kruse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFiguring%20out%20how%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShane%2C%2037%2C%20is%20about%20to%20lose%20his%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Marine%20Corps%20veteran%2C%20who%20has%20driven%20for%20Lyft%20and%20Uber%20for%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20has%20various%20medical%20issues%20that%20limit%20how%20much%20he%20can%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShane%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20said%20driving%20to%20more%20urban%20areas%20is%20the%20best%20he%20can%20do%2C%20given%20he%20recently%20lost%20his%20full-time%20job%20due%20to%20his%20medical%20issues%20and%20hasn't%20had%20any%20leads%20on%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20few%20tips%20and%20earnings%20that%20don't%20meet%20what%20he%20and%20his%20family%20need%2C%20he%20said%20he%20isn't%20sure%20what%20his%20next%20steps%20will%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20we%20aren't%20getting%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20Shane%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20trying%20to%20make%20money%20with%20rideshare%20driving%20but%20with%20no%20luck%2C%20even%20with%20researching%20ideas%20and%20trying%20different%20avenues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20disabled%20gig%20drivers%20with%20medical%20issues%2C%20gig%20work%20is%20a%20temporary%20but%20necessary%20step%20toward%20getting%20back%20on%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERene%2C%2048%2C%20an%20Air%20Force%20veteran%20with%20a%20debilitating%20back%20injury%2C%20has%20driven%20for%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-hours-uber-lyft-drivers-work-taxi-competitive-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Lyft%20and%20Uber%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Denver%20area%20for%20a%20few%20months%20after%20holding%20full-time%20jobs%20in%20real%20estate.%20She%20couldn't%20work%20a%209-to-5%20due%20to%20her%20medical%20issues%20and%20resorts%20to%20gig%20driving%20to%20earn%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20driving%20becomes%20more%20painful%2C%20she%20said%20she%20can't%20secure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-money-gig-worker-uber-lyft-doordash-delivery-driver-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20full-time%20positions%20that%20pay%20better%20and%20fit%20her%20needs.%20She%20said%20she%20can%20only%20drive%20between%20two%20and%20four%20hours%20at%20a%20time%20and%20needs%20to%20take%20recovery%20days%20after%20longer%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20low%20earnings%20have%20forced%20her%20to%20give%20up%20her%20apartment%20and%20move%20in%20with%20her%20family%20while%20she%20searches%20for%20more%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20life%2C%20no%20self-care%2C%20exercise.%20There's%20no%20time%20for%20relationships%20because%20your%20whole%20day%20is%20spent%20managing%20the%20pain%20and%20then%20trying%20to%20squeeze%20in%20hours%20to%20pay%20the%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20Rene%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20medical%20issues%20that%20put%20them%20out%20of%20work%20are%20also%20often%20prevented%20from%20reentering%20the%20traditional%20workforce.%20Richard%20H.%20drove%20for%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-help-loneliness-gig-economy-work-las-vegas-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Phoenix%20area%20for%20eight%20years%20before%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20leukemia%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202021.%20He%20noticed%20it%20was%20harder%20to%20make%20the%20amount%20needed%20to%20live%20comfortably%20after%20he%20started%20driving%20again%20in%20early%202023%20%E2%80%94%20after%201%20%C2%BD%20years%20of%20chemotherapy%20and%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20said%20he's%20now%20searching%20for%20a%20full-time%20job%20because%20he's%20still%20not%20comfortable%20with%20the%20amount%20he%20makes%20driving%20six%20to%20seven%20days%20a%20week%20from%206%20p.m.%20to%202%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20pay%20us%20enough%20for%20us%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20a%20decent%20living%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Richard%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BBack%20then%2C%20I'd%20go%20out%20for%20three%20to%20four%20hours%20and%20make%20%24400%20when%20I%20first%20started.%20Now%2C%20you%20have%20to%20go%20out%20and%20work%2010%20to%2014%20hours%20to%20try%20to%20make%20%24300.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20toward%20stability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20disabled%20gig%20drivers%20are%20searching%20for%20ways%20to%20achieve%20more%20stability%2C%20whether%20that%20means%20going%20back%20to%20school%2C%20building%20up%20experience%20in%20other%20fields%2C%20or%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20help%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%2C%20in%20his%20late%2030s%2C%20made%20over%20%24110%2C000%20in%20gross%20earnings%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-hours-uber-lyft-drivers-work-taxi-competitive-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20driving%20for%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20Jersey%20in%202022.%20This%20was%20reduced%20to%20just%20%2414%2C000%20after%20taking%20out%20commissions%20to%20the%20ride-hailing%20companies%2C%20taxes%2C%20and%20other%20expenses.%20This%20amount%20wasn't%20sufficient%20to%20cover%20expenses%2C%20including%20rent%2C%20childcare%2C%20utilities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20treatmen