si.com%2Fnfl%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2F49ers-brock-purdy-opens-living-teammate-nick-zakelj%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20with%20a%20roommate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20teammate%20Nick%20Zakelj.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-salaries-quarterbacks-super-bowl-contracts-patrick-mahomes-lamar-jackson-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706440081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b407f9f4b446f3be9d5bfa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-salaries-quarterbacks-super-bowl-contracts-patrick-mahomes-lamar-jackson-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20four%20quarterbacks%20taking%20their%20teams%20to%20the%20playoffs%2C%20there%20is%20a%20large%20divide%20among%20what%20they%20make%20and%20that%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20advantage%20for%20NFL%20teams.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cgaines%40insider.com%20(Cork%20Gaines)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-salaries-quarterbacks-super-bowl-contracts-patrick-mahomes-lamar-jackson-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nitish's%20INDIA%20Exit%3A%20Why%20the%20Blame%20Rests%20on%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20days%20of%20speculation%2C%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20resigned%20from%20his%20position%20Sunday%20morning%2C%20after%20his%20party%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20decided%20to%20end%20its%20alliance%20with%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20form%20a%20new%20government%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20rumours%20that%20Nitish%20may%20join%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20again%20had%20been%20rife%20but%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20silence%20over%20the%20matter%2C%20even%20as%20he%20publicly%20expressed%20his%20anguish%20over%20lack%20of%20any%20progress%20in%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20at%20least%20twice%2C%20left%20the%20political%20pot%20boiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20submitting%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20Rajendra%20Arlekar%2C%20on%20Sunday%20morning%20that%20Nitish%20confirmed%20all%20rumours%2C%20giving%20little%20chance%20to%20his%20former%20allies%20in%20INDIA%20to%20negotiate%2C%20cajole%20or%20convince%20him%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20opposition%20alliance.%20This%20lent%20further%20credence%20to%20the%20impression%20that%20Nitish%20had%20already%20decided%20to%20part%20ways%20with%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20resigned%20as%20CM%20today%20and%20have%20asked%20the%20Governor%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20government.%20Party%20leaders%20were%20giving%20me%20advice.%20I%20heard%20what%20they%20said%20and%20have%20resigned.%20The%20situation%20was%20not%20good.%20So%2C%20we%20have%20broken%20ties%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitish%20said%20in%20his%20usual%20taciturn%20style%20while%20announcing%20his%20decision%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20working%20on%20an%20alliance%20(INDIA)%20for%20the%20last%201.5%20years%20but%20things%20were%20not%20working%20out.%20Now%2C%20we%20will%20form%20a%20new%20alliance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20the%20past%2C%20when%20he%20similarly%20switched%20camps%2C%20he%20evaded%20appearing%20in%20the%20public%20to%20clarify%20doubts%2C%20remained%20unreachable%20to%20his%20allies%20who%20attempted%20to%20contact%20him%20multiple%20times%2C%20and%20focused%20solely%20on%20mapping%20out%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20deal%20with%20the%20saffron%20party%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChasing%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20political%20ambitions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Nitish%20secured%20his%20first%20full-term%20tenure%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%202005%2C%20he%20has%20barely%20been%20in%20an%20oppositional%20space.%20Barring%20a%20few%20months%20here%20and%20there%2C%20every%20decision%20that%20the%20septuagenarian%20leader%20took%20reasserted%20his%20own%20indispensability%20in%20Bihar%2C%20even%20when%20making%20new%20alliances.%20He%20has%20survived%2C%20and%20survived%20beyond%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20imagination%2C%20while%20remaining%20in%20power%20or%20pulling%20the%20strings%20of%20power%20ceaselessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20Nitish%20had%20his%20own%20political%20ambitions%20in%20mind%20every%20time%20he%20switched%20camps.%20He%20remained%20with%20the%20BJP%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20primary%20rival%20RJD%20in%20Bihar%20for%20years%2C%20but%20ended%20this%20alliance%20as%20he%20could%20foresee%20the%20fate%20of%20allies%20with%20the%20seemingly%20totalitarian%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ascent%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Nitish%20recharged%20his%20own%20position%20by%20quitting%20the%20NDA%20and%20beating%20the%20BJP%20with%20the%20help%20of%20its%20arch%20rival%20RJD%20in%20the%202015%20state%20assembly%20polls.%20Having%20delivered%20a%20striking%20message%20to%20Modi%20about%20his%20political%20significance%2C%20he%20went%20back%20to%20the%20NDA%20where%20he%20had%20been%20the%20most%20comfortable%20in%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20relationship%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20however%2C%20took%20the%20biggest%20hit%20when%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%20allegedly%20engineered%20substantial%20losses%20for%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Lok%20Janshakti%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Chirag%20Paswan%20in%20the%202020%20assembly%20polls.%20BJP%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20state%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20ended%20up%20with%20its%20best%20tally%20(74)%2C%20while%20Janata%20Dal%20finished%20with%20one%20of%20its%20worst%20performances%20as%20a%20NDA%20constituent%20with%20merely%2043%20seats.%20Things%20took%20a%20final%20hit%20when%20he%20lost%20his%20closest%20aide%20R.C.P.%20Singh%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Singh%20was%20swiftly%20made%20a%20Union%20minister%2C%20even%20as%20the%20BJP%20attempted%20to%20poach%20JD(U)%E2%80%99s%20legislators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20only%20prominent%20BJP%20ally%20in%20India%20as%20others%20like%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(Badal)%20or%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20had%20already%20left%20the%20NDA%20because%20of%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20disregard%20for%20alliance%20politics.%20Yet%2C%20Nitish%20survived%20by%20quickly%20joining%20ranks%20with%20the%20RJD%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20national%20goal%20to%20help%20create%20a%20larger%20opposition%20front%20against%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20is%20now%20back%20in%20the%20NDA%2C%20masterfully%20securing%20his%20position%20as%20the%20most%20valuable%20ally%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Bihar%20yet%20again.%20The%20saffron%20party%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20missed%20a%20window%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20Nitish%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Its%20senior%20leaders%20hit%20out%20at%20Nitish%20on%20almost%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20with%20even%20the%20prime%20minister%20lashing%20out%20at%20him%20quite%20a%20few%20times%20in%20his%20speeches.%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20compared%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejungle%20raaj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20BJP%20leaders%20built%20a%20campaign%20around%20alleged%20corruption%2C%20misgovernance%2C%20and%20failing%20law%20and%20order%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20Nitish%20operated%20through%20this%20mesh%20of%20political%20dynamics%20is%20known%2C%20but%20by%20accepting%20him%20again%2C%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20prioritises%20its%20electoral%20ambitions%20much%20more%20than%20its%20rhetoric%20of%20good%20governance%20and%20political%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20big%20blow%20for%20INDIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20he%20had%20handed%20over%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20reins%20to%20his%20deputy%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%2C%20while%20touring%20the%20country%20to%20bring%20together%20a%20range%20of%20regional%20and%20national%20parties%20under%20a%20common%20umbrella.%20Most%20of%20these%20parties%20have%20been%20historically%20inimical%20to%20the%20Congress.%20Bringing%20them%20all%20together%20to%20ally%20with%20the%20Congress%20required%20negotiations%20that%20only%20a%20senior%20leader%20with%20political%20acumen%20like%20Nitish%20could%20have%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20he%20was%20instrumental%20in%20conducting%20a%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar%2C%20which%20gave%20a%20fillip%20to%20the%20opposition%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20Congress.%20The%20demand%20for%20a%20pan-India%20caste%20census%20re-energised%20Mandal%20politics%20and%20put%20the%20BJP%20on%20the%20backfoot%2C%20even%20if%20temporarily.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Nitish%20government%20foregrounded%20issues%20like%20employment%20and%20welfare%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%20by%20appointing%20over%20three%20lakh%20youth%20in%20state%20government%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20success%20of%20INDIA%20as%20a%20front%2C%20that%20also%20fended%20off%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20third%20front%20in%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20displayed%20his%20frustration%20with%20its%20lack%20of%20progress.%20His%20first%20dissent%20came%20in%20November%202023%20when%20he%20showed%20his%20anguish%20over%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffor-india-to-work-the-congress-must-take-a-step-back%5C%22%3Elethargic%20approach%20towards%20the%20opposition%20front%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20grand-old%20party%E2%80%99s%20sole%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20assembly%20polls%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20lost%20all%20the%20three%20Hindi-heartland%20states%2C%20despite%20showing%20great%20confidence%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20polls.%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20needs%20to%20take%20the%20blame%20in%20triggering%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20they%20will%20have%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20ministers%20of%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Delhi%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20The%20two%20leaders%20mooted%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20in%20the%20long-delayed%20INDIA%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20December%2019%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20called%20by%20the%20Congress%20was%20supposed%20to%20happen%20on%20December%206%2C%202023%20but%20leaders%20like%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%20expressed%20their%20unavailability%2C%20indicating%20their%20discomfort%20with%20the%20alliance.%20Then%2C%20when%20the%20meeting%20happened%20eventually%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20surprisingly%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20Kharge%20as%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20without%20discussing%20it%20with%20any%20of%20the%20other%20leaders.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Congress%20was%20recovering%20from%20its%20losses%20in%20assembly%20elections%20and%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20explaining%20to%20do%20in%20front%20of%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20discussions%20on%20prime%20ministerial%20candidates%20appeared%20to%20be%20premature%2C%20when%20basics%20like%20seat-sharing%2C%20campaign%20strategy%20and%20joint%20action%20programmes%20had%20not%20been%20finalised.%20The%20fact%20that%20TMC%20spokespersons%20went%20on%20record%20after%20the%20fourth%20INDIA%20meeting%20on%20December%2019%20to%20suggest%20that%20INDIA%20will%20finalise%20seat-sharing%20by%20December%2031%20also%20looked%20improbable%2C%20forcing%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20general%20secretary%20(organisation)%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20and%20RJD%20chief%20Lalu%20Prasad%20to%20refute%20the%20TMC%20in%20their%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20recall%20how%20Nitish%20had%20braved%20media%20questions%20on%20a%20probable%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20when%20he%20was%20meeting%20leaders%20to%20formalise%20the%20alliance.%20Having%20known%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20preference%20to%20reduce%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9CModi%20vs%20%E2%80%98who%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20presidential%20style%2C%20Nitish%20had%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20in%20INDIA%20and%20persistently%20maintained%20that%20the%20alliance%20will%20fight%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20by%20highlighting%20the%20concerns%20of%20common%20people%20and%20canvassing%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20authoritarian%20and%20centralising%20impulses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mischievous%20moves%20by%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20have%20now%20made%20their%20minds%20clear%20by%20announcing%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20alliance%20with%20the%20Congress%20in%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Punjab%2C%20undermined%20Nitish%20and%20other%20regional%20leaders%20of%20INDIA%2C%20and%20created%20a%20political%20narrative%20that%20was%20vastly%20different%20from%20what%20INDIA%20leaders%20had%20originally%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20Nitish%20had%20already%20expressed%20his%20view%20about%20the%20supposed%20%E2%80%9Clack%20of%20seriousness%E2%80%9D%20in%20India%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20hasty%20decision%20to%20train%20its%20energy%20on%20the%20second%20round%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20even%20before%20the%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20strategy%20was%20chalked%20out%2C%20may%20have%20come%20as%20a%20final%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20has%20not%20bothered%20with%20monikers%20like%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ekursi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chair)%20Kumar%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20%E2%80%9Cpaltu%20ram%E2%80%9D%20thrown%20at%20him%20ever%20in%20his%20political%20career.%20He%20has%20never%20owned%20ideological%20ethics.%20He%20has%20rather%20taken%20pride%20in%20his%20pragmatism%20and%20effectiveness.%20With%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20formidable%20opposition%20alliance%20in%20Bihar%20and%20its%2040%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20has%20broken.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20too%2C%20will%20sorely%20miss%20his%20strategic%20thinking%20and%20political%20acumen%20in%20taking%20on%20the%20dominant%20BJP.%20Nitish%20could%20have%20been%20an%20asset%20for%20the%20alliance%2C%20given%20his%20deep%20political%20experience%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706439998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20non-profit%20behind%20Wikipedia%20and%20a%20crypto%20exchange%20are%20among%20the%20top%20companies%20for%20work-from-anywhere%20jobs%2C%20with%20some%20paying%20over%20%24100%2C000%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22