owerPoint%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20apology%20%E2%80%94%20he%20talks%20too%20much.%20From%20there%2C%20he%20tells%20the%20young%20pitcher%20about%20his%20life%20in%20the%20game%2C%20about%20the%20way%20players%20struggle%20financially%20%E2%80%94%20he%20once%20watched%20a%20teammate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffishwife-becca-millstein-caroline-goldfarb-split-lawsuit-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efish%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20a%20dumpster%20for%20food%20%E2%80%94%20and%20about%20the%20superstars%20he%20met%20who%20earned%20more%20millions%20than%20they%20could%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20Schwimer%2C%20who%20suddenly%20found%20his%20baseball%20career%20derailed%20by%20an%20injury%2C%20hit%20on%20an%20idea.%20What%20if%20athletes%20could%20sell%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20future%20earnings%20to%20investors%2C%20the%20same%20way%20tech%20entrepreneurs%20offer%20a%20stake%20in%20their%20promising%20new%20ideas%20in%20return%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvcs-funding-startups-disrupt-future-entertainment-generative-ai-tech-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eventure%20capital%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20What%20is%20a%20minor-league%20pitcher%2C%20after%20all%2C%20if%20not%20a%20one-man%20startup%20aiming%20to%20break%20into%20the%20big%20leagues%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%202016%2C%20Schwimer%20started%20Big%20League%20Advantage%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20hedge%20fund%20that%20invests%20in%20the%20future%20of%20minor-league%20baseball%20players.%20Following%20a%20landmark%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ncaa-third-party-endorsement-startups-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20that%20allowed%20student%20athletes%20to%20be%20paid%2C%20BLA%20has%20since%20expanded%20to%20invest%20in%20college%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeacock-nfl-playoff-stream-drew-millions-subscribers-report-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efootball%3C%2Fa%3E%20players%2C%20basketball%20players%2C%20hockey%20players%2C%20and%20coaches.%20(Schwimer%20explains%20that%20BLA%20also%20hopes%20to%20invest%20in%20musicians.%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20signed%20any%20yet%2C%20but%20anybody%20who%20wants%20a%20deal%20with%20us%2C%20we%20want%20to%20call%20us.%26quot%3B)%20Using%20a%20proprietary%20algorithm%20monitored%20by%20some%2030%20analysts%2C%20the%20firm%20models%20a%20player's%20career%20earnings%20to%20decide%20how%20much%20to%20invest%20in%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20look%20at%20the%20game%20very%2C%20very%20differently%20than%20everyone%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20tells%20the%20pitcher.%20%26quot%3BWe%20probably%20spend%20more%20money%20on%20our%20analytics%20team%20than%20multiple%20teams%20combined.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Schwimer%20says%2C%20BLA%20has%20invested%20in%20the%20future%20earnings%20of%20nearly%20600%20players.%20The%20athlete%20%E2%80%94%20often%20a%20teenager%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0gets%20an%20up-front%20payment%20in%20return%20for%20up%20to%2015%25%20of%20their%20professional%20sports%20earnings%20over%20the%20next%2025%20years.%20Schwimer%20says%20the%20payments%20start%20around%20%24100%2C000%20and%20sometimes%20range%20into%20the%20millions.%20One%20of%20the%20fund's%20first%20deals%20was%20with%20the%20hot-shot%20shortstop%20Fernando%20Tatis%20Jr.%2C%20an%2018-year-old%20who%20went%20on%20to%20sign%20a%2014-year%20deal%20with%20the%20San%20Diego%20Padres%20for%20%24340%20million.%20If%20BLA%20secured%20only%208%25%20of%20his%20earnings%2C%20Tatis%20alone%20would%20pay%20out%20%2427.2%20million%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20the%20company%20raised%20in%20its%20initial%20round%20of%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%2020%20minutes%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-different-company-remote-working-return-to-office-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZoom%3C%2Fa%3E%20call%2C%20Schwimer%20arrives%20at%20what%20the%20pitcher%20and%20his%20wife%20have%20been%20waiting%20for%3A%20an%20offer.%20BLA%2C%20he%20announces%2C%20will%20pay%20the%20pitcher%20%2412%2C000%20for%20each%20percent%20of%20his%20future%20earnings%2C%20up%20to%20%24180%2C000.%20That's%20a%20nice%20chunk%20of%20change%20for%20a%20young%20couple.%20But%20if%20he%20winds%20up%20making%20it%20big%2C%20the%20pitcher%20could%20be%20selling%20tens%20of%20millions%20in%20earnings%20to%20BLA%20for%20pennies%20on%20the%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssume%20you're%20gonna%20make%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20urges%20the%20player.%20%26quot%3BAssume%20you're%20gonna%20be%20great.%20We've%20only%20had%20two%20players%20regret%20it%20later.%20If%20you're%20not%20gonna%20be%20happy%2C%20please%20don't%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20call%2C%20the%20pitcher%20%E2%80%94%20who%20agreed%20to%20let%20me%20join%20on%20the%20condition%20he%20remain%20anonymous%20%E2%80%94%20asks%20Schwimer%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20he%20says%20no%20now.%20Is%20there%20a%20chance%20there%20will%20be%20a%20higher%20offer%20next%20year%20if%20he%20performs%20well%20on%20the%20field%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20has%20anticipated%20the%20question.%20Ninety-two%20percent%20of%20the%20time%2C%20he%20tells%20the%20pitcher%2C%20the%20offer%20will%20wind%20up%20being%20lower.%20And%2080%20percent%20of%20the%20time%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20offer%20at%20all.%20The%20message%20is%20clear%3A%20If%20the%20couple%20wants%20the%20%24180%2C000%2C%20it's%20now%20or%20never.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20is%20far%20from%20alone%20in%20treating%20human%20beings%20as%20growth%20investments.%20X10%20Capital%2C%20run%20by%20one%20of%20the%20original%20general%20partners%20at%20Benchmark%20Capital%2C%20offers%20similar%20deals%20to%20athletes.%20Finlete%20is%20launching%20a%20fund%20that%20allows%20fans%20to%20buy%20shares%20in%20a%20prospect's%20future%20earn