20cut%20are%20like%20any%20successful%20founder%20who%20owes%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-important-venture-capitalists-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eventure-capital%3C%2Fa%3E%20firm%20its%20cut%3B%20those%20who%20don't%20are%20lucky%20enough%20to%20grab%20a%20little%20financial%20security%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20toughest%20and%20most%20inequitable%20job%20markets.%20And%20though%20he%20has%20raised%20nearly%20%24250%20million%20in%20funding%20to%20invest%20in%20promising%20young%20athletes%2C%20he%20sees%20himself%20as%20a%20misunderstood%20underdog%20fighting%20on%20behalf%20of%20other%20underdogs.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20start%20this%20company%20for%20agents%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20start%20this%20company%20for%20journalists.%20I%20started%20this%20company%20by%20players%2C%20for%20players.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20November%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20day%20with%20Schwimer%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20where%20he%20was%20speaking%20to%20business-school%20students%20and%20alumni%20at%20the%20Wharton%20Sports%20Business%20Summit.%20Over%20breakfast%2C%20he%20tells%20me%20he%20still%20remembers%20the%20moment%20he%20knew%20he'd%20never%20be%20an%20MLB%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20after%20four%20years%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia%2C%20he%20was%20drafted%20in%20the%2014th%20round.%20When%20Schwimer%20arrived%20at%20his%20first%20minor-league%20workout%2C%20he%20watched%20pitcher%20after%20pitcher%20throw%20fastballs%20that%20whizzed%20and%20breaking%20balls%20that%20snapped%20in%20ways%20his%20never%20had.%20That%20day%2C%20he%20called%20his%20dad%2C%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20trouble%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20no%20shot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20dad%20was%20unperturbed.%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20be%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Schwimer%20started%20thinking%20analytically.%20He'd%20spent%20a%20summer%20interning%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fhedge-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehedge%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20P.A.W.%20Partners%2C%20where%20he'd%20worked%20with%20their%20trading%20algorithms.%20To%20better%20understand%20the%20tendencies%20of%20the%20hitters%20he'd%20be%20facing%2C%20he%20built%20a%20rudimentary%20model.%20The%20data%2C%20he%20says%2C%20revealed%20that%20hitters%20are%20shockingly%20predictable%20creatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20had%20four%20subpar%20pitches.%20But%20informed%20by%20his%20DIY%20pitch-selection%20algorithm%2C%20he%20managed%20to%20confuse%20batters%20enough%20to%20move%20up%20through%20the%20Phillies%20organization.%20He%20claims%20he%20got%20the%20nickname%20Houdini%20because%20no%20one%20could%20understand%20how%20he%20was%20sneaking%20his%20pitches%20by%20all%20these%20batters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Schwimer's%20teammates%20dubbed%20his%20penchant%20for%20wild%20theories%20and%20seeking%20creative%20edges%20%26quot%3BSchwimosophy.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6ad266979d7371823896a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchwimer's%20teammates%20dubbed%20his%20penchant%20for%20wild%20theories%20and%20seeking%20creative%20edges%20%26quot%3BSchwimosophy.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EChristian%20Petersen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20is%20vintage%20Schwimer%20%E2%80%94%20a%20slightly%20self-promotional%20tale%20that%20looks%20shaky%20on%20closer%20inspection.%20When%20I%20asked%20Erik%20Kratz%2C%20who%20was%20Schwimer's%20catcher%20in%20AAA%2C%20about%20the%20Houdini%20moniker%2C%20he%20responded%20with%20a%20laugh.%20%26quot%3BIs%20that%20a%20self-proclaimed%20nickname%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20better%20go%20back%20to%20him%20and%20see%20if%20he's%20talking%20about%20himself%20in%20the%20third%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20insisted%20the%20story%20was%20true%20%E2%80%94%20mostly.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20would%20say%20all%20the%20time%3A%20'You're%20like%20fucking%20Houdini.%20How%20the%20fuck%20are%20you%20getting%20outs%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20clarified%20when%20I%20went%20back%20to%20him.%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%20yeah%2C%20I%20guess%20it%20probably%20was%20a%20little%20aggressive%20to%20say%20it%20was%20my%20nickname.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKratz%20says%20Schwimer%20developed%20a%20contentious%20reputation%20on%20his%20team%20for%20%26quot%3Bquestioning%20things%26quot%3B%20and%20seeking%20creative%20edges.%20Once%2C%20he%20annoyed%20every%20hitter%20in%20the%20dugout%20when%20he%20shared%20his%20idea%20to%20train%20one%20of%20them%20to%20foul%20off%20a%20dozen%20pitches%20per%20at%20bat%2C%20to%20tire%20out%20the%20opposing%20pitcher.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20just%20like%2C%20'Schwim%2C%20are%20you%20kidding%20me%3F%20You're%20completely%20demeaning%20what%20we%20do%20every%20single%20day%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kratz%20recalls.%20Kratz%20tells%20me%20they%20dubbed%20Schwimer's%20wild%20theories%20Schwimosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Schwimer%20was%20drafted%2C%20his%20friends%20from%20home%20thought%20he%20was%20rich.%20%26quot%3BI%20signed%20for%203.2%2C%26quot%3B%20he'd%20tell%20them%2C%20pausing%20for%20dramatic%20effect.%20%26quot%3BThousand.%20After%20tax.%26quot%3B%20He%20saw%20the%20precarious%20financial%20conditions%20that%20up-and-coming%20players%20face%20firsthand.%20When%20one%20top%20prospect%20in%20the%20Arizona%20Fall%20League%20told%20him%20that%20the%20stress%20of%20supporting%20his%20wife%20and%20baby%20was%20hurting%20his%20play%2C%20Schwimer%20says%20he%20floated%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20model%20for%20BLA.%20What%20if%20you%20could%20sell%20a%20share%20of%20your%20future%20earnings%2C%20he%20asked%2C%20for%20%2410%2C000%3F%20%26quot%3BI'd%20give%20up%2050%25%20for%2010%20grand!%26quot%3B%20the%20guy%20joked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20when%20Schwimer%20got%20the%20call%20to%20join%20the%20Phillies%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20the%20Motel%206%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fhotels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERitz%20Carlton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20overnight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20In%20an%20anecdote%20he%20often%20deploys%20in%20his%20sales%20pitches%2C%20he%20recounts%20hanging%20out%20with%20the%20All-Star%20starter%20Cole%20Hamels.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20have%20%24120%20million%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked%20the%20pitcher.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamels%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20do%20anything%20I%20want%20in%20the%20offseason%2C%20but%20it's%20incrementally%20useless.%20If%20I%20had%20made%20%24110%20million%2C%20there'd%20be%20zero%20difference%20in%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%20(Hamels%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exchange%2C%20as%20Schwimer%20tells%20it%2C%20got%20him%20thinking.%20Soon%20after%2C%20he%20tore%20his%20labrum%20and%20faced%20a%20year%20of%20rehab.%20He%20fell%20into%20a%20depression%2C%20spending%20his%20days%20on%20the%20couch%20reading%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgame-of-thrones-prequel-spinoff-plans-timeline-hbo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGame%20of%20Thrones%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Finally%2C%20prodded%20by%20his%20wife%2C%20he%20started%20tinkering%20with%20his%20hitters%20algorithm%2C%20transforming%20it%20into%20a%20tool%20to%20rank%20the%20career%20prospects%20of%20every%20minor-league%20player.%20In%20a%20%26quot%3BMoneyball%26quot%3B%20moment%2C%20he%20discovered%20that%20his%20model%20didn't%20jibe%20with%20the%20MLB's%20official%20rankings.%20Today%2C%20he%20says%2C%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20the%20players%20BLA%20has%20invested%20in%20are%20outside%20the%20league's%20top%20300%20prospects.%20I%20ask%20if%20signing%20lower-level%20candidates%20is%20a%20conscious%20choice%20to%20maximize%20value.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we%20just%20think%20the%20rankings%20are%20terrible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224837%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fernando%20Tatis%20Jr.%20of%20the%20San%20Diego%20Padres%20reacts%20after%20hitting%20a%20solo%20homerun%20during%20%20MLB%20World%20Tour%20Mexico%20City%20Series%20in%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6ac0a6979d737182388f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223225%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFernando%20Tatis%20Jr.%20signed%20with%20BLA%20when%20he%20was%2018.%3Cp%3ESean%20M.%20Haffey%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20two%20years%20in%20the%20MLB%2C%20Schwimer%20had%20accumulated%20wealthy%20contacts.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20you%20get%20to%20the%20major%20leagues%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbillionaires%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20wanna%20hang%20out%20with%20you%20and%20play%20some%20golf.%26quot%3B%20The%20guys%20he%20met%20on%20the%20links%20gave%20him%20the%20capital%20for%20his%20first%20fund.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%2C%20heaviest%20hitters%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20told%20the%20husband%20and%20wife%20on%20the%20Zoom%20call.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20over%20200%20of%20them%20with%20a%20combined%20net%20worth%20over%20%24100%20billion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMembers%20of%20BLA's%20board%20have%20included%20Marvin%20Bush%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20and%20Paul%20DePodesta%2C%20the%20Cleveland%20Browns%20executive%20who%20features%20heavily%20in%20%26quot%3BMoneyball.%26quot%3B%20One%20of%20the%20billionaire%20investors%20who%20helped%20bankroll%20BLA's%20first%20fund%20was%20Bill%20Miller%2C%20who%20was%20famously%20early%20and%20bullish%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-openai-policy-ai-generated-product-listings-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20rate%20of%20return%20Schwimer%20promised%20was%20astronomical.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20gonna%20be%20pretty%20hard%20not%20to%20make%20money%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20told%20HBO's%20%26quot%3BReal%20Sports.%26quot%3B%20The%20data%20that%20Michael%20showed%20us%20was%20at%20least%2030%25%20a%20year%20for%2020%20years%20or%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beauty%20of%20the%20model%2C%20from%20an%20investor's%20perspective%2C%20is%20the%20way%20it%20places%20relatively%20small%20bets%20that%20offer%20the%20prospect%20of%20huge%20outcomes.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20only%20lose%20the%20money%20we%20give%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20we%20can%20make%20a%2050%20times%20return.%26quot%3B%20As%20in%20venture%20capital%2C%20a%20single%20unicorn%20can%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20many%2C%20many%20bad%20bets.%20The%20key%20then%20is%20to%20identify%20promising%20players%20and%20correctly%20price%20their%20future%20earnings.%20And%20with%20baseball%20salaries%20soaring%2C%20betting%20long%20on%20sports%20contracts%20has%20an%20obvious%20appeal.%20In%201999%2C%20baseball's%20top-paid%20player%20brought%20home%20just%20under%20%2412%20million.%20Today%2C%20the%20Dodgers%20will%20pay%20Shohei%20Ohtani%20%2470%20million%20a%20year%20for%20the%20next%20decade.%20Even%20if%2070%20to%2080%20percent%20of%20BLA's%20investments%20never%20bear%20fruit%2C%20as%20Schwimer%20estimates%2C%20owning%2015%25%20of%20a%20star%20player's%20future%20earnings%20is%20like%20holding%20a%20share%20in%20something%20that%20%E2%80%94%20if%20the%20last%20half%20century%20is%20any%20guide%20%E2%80%94%20will%20only%20go%20up%2C%20and%20up%2C%20and%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20walk%20from%20the%20diner%20to%20Penn's%20campus%2C%20Schwimer%20tells%20me%20that%20there's%20no%20difference%20between%20a%20startup%20founder%20taking%20an%20investment%20in%20exchange%20for%20equity%20and%20a%20young%20athlete%20taking%20an%20investment%20from%20him.%20He%20mentions%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-life-career-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJeff%20Bezos%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20up%2020%25%20of%20Amazon%20for%20%241%20million%20back%20in%201995%2C%20and%20today%2C%20post-divorce%2C%20Bezos%20owns%20only%2010%25%20of%20his%20company.%20He%20tells%20me%20he%20controls%20only%2052%25%20of%20BLA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJeff%20Bezos%20gave%2080%25!%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20gave%20up%2048%25!%20Was%20I%20taken%20advantage%20of%3F%20Was%20Jeff%20Bezos%20taken%20advantage%20of%3F%20Would%20anyone%20possibly%20say%20that%3F%20It's%20crazy%20to%20me.%20And%20nobody%20to%20this%20day%20has%20ever%20shown%20me%20any%20possible%20way%20as%20to%20why%20it's%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20issue%2C%20I%20explain%2C%20is%20that%20the%20public%20has%20always%20balked%20at%20businessmen%20profiting%20off%20an%20athlete's%20excellence.%20Agents%20and%20owners%20are%20not%20exactly%20beloved.%20Schwimer%20dismisses%20such%20concerns%20as%20reflexively%20anti-business.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20a%20company%20that%20makes%20%242%20billion%2C%20we%20are%20fucking%20over%20athletes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20a%20company%20that%20loses%20all%20our%20money%2C%20we%20do%20great%20for%20athletes.%20Well%2C%20that's%20bullshit.%20That's%20like%20if%20you%20invest%20in%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20you%20lose%2C%20you're%20great%20for%20the%20economy.%20But%20if%20you%20win%2C%20you're%20taking%20advantage%20of%20everybody.%20It's%20insane.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20admit%20to%20Schwimer%20that%20I'd%20been%20feeling%20a%20certain%20queasiness%20about%20his%20company%20that%20I'd%20been%20trying%20to%20unpack.%20The%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20often%20investing%20in%20teenagers%2C%20seemingly%20in%20times%20of%20need%2C%20was%20something%20I%20couldn't%20square%20morally.%20People%20have%20long%20circled%20young%20stars%20with%20dubious%20or%20exploitative%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eoffers%2C%20financial%20or%20otherwise%2C%20I%20point%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAthletes%20are%20thought%20of%20as%20dumb%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20responds.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20God%2C%20it%20just%20kills%20me.%20Like%2C%20it's%20an%20%3Cem%3Eism%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Not%20racism%3B%20it's%20like%20intelligent-ism.%20Do%20you%20know%20how%20hard%20it%20was%20for%20me%20to%20start%20this%20thing%3F%20I'm%20going%20in%20with%2010%20legs%20down.%20I'm%20a%20former%20baseball%20player.%20They%20all%20assume%20I'm%20a%20moron.%20Like%2C%20it's%20hard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20is%20protective%20of%20BLA's%20algorithm%2C%20which%20he%20believes%20provides%20him%20with%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecompetitive%20edge.%20He%20would%20only%20share%20certain%20small%20differentiators%2C%20like%20the%20way%20the%20model%20puts%20more%20weight%20on%20how%20a%20minor-league%20hitter%20performs%20against%20an%20elite%20pitcher%20than%20how%20he%20performs%20against%20guys%20who%20will%20never%20make%20it%20to%20the%20show.%20Steven%20Duncker%2C%20a%20former%20Goldman%20Sachs%20partner%20who%20sits%20on%20BLA's%20board%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eadmits%20he%20doesn't%20fully%20understand%20how%20the%20model%20works%2C%20but%20nevertheless%20believes%20they're%20onto%20something%20game-changing.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20'Moneyball'-plus%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20say%2C%20'You%20know%20the%20advantage%20is%20going%20to%20go%20away%3F'%20I'm%20shocked%20it%20hasn't.%20But%20it%20really%20hasn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223268%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elly%20De%20La%20Cruz%20%2344%20of%20the%20Cincinnati%20Reds%20takes%20the%20field%20for%20warmups%20before%20the%20game%20against%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Dodgers%20at%20Great%20American%20Ball%20Park%20on%20June%2006%2C%202023%20in%20Cincinnati%2C%20Ohio.%20De%20La%20Cruz%2C%20the%20%234%20MLB%20prospect%2C%20was%20called%20up%20for%20the%20game.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6ae596979d737182389e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222178%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20say%20rookie%20shortstop%20Elly%20De%20La%20Cruz%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20make%20%24500%20million.%20%26quot%3BHe%20might%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20also%20might%20not%20make%20%242%20million.%20He%20could%20get%20hit%20by%20a%20bus.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EDylan%20Buell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20some%20obvious%20hazards%20to%20betting%20on%20a%20person%20instead%20of%20a%20company.%20Tatis%2C%20the%20shortstop%20whom%20BLA%20is%20banking%20on%2C%20was%20suspended%20in%202022%20for%2080%20games%20without%20pay%20after%20testing%20positive%20for%20a%20performance-enhancing%20drug.%20Two%20more%20offenses%20would%20result%20in%20a%20lifetime%20ban.%20%26quot%3BThree%20of%20our%20players%20under%20the%20age%20of%2025%20have%20died%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Schwimer.%20%26quot%3BBut%20now%2C%20at%20least%2C%20their%20families%20have%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%20People%20tell%20Schwimer%20that%20Elly%20De%20La%20Cruz%2C%20the%20rookie%20shortstop%20phenom%20who%20signed%20with%20BLA%20while%20in%20the%20minors%2C%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20make%20%24500%20million.%20%26quot%3BHe%20might%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20also%20might%20not%20make%20%242%20million.%20He%20could%20get%20hit%20by%20a%20bus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20all%20his%20talk%20about%20how%20athletes%20are%20derided%20as%20unintelligent%2C%20there%20is%20one%20type%20of%20player%20whose%20thought%20process%20Schwimer%20questions%3A%20those%20who%20choose%20not%20to%20sign%20with%20BLA.%20Schwimer%20claims%20he%20now%20has%20enough%20data%20to%20prove%20that%20if%20two%20players%20are%20ranked%20equally%20by%20the%20algorithm%2C%20and%20one%20takes%20money%20from%20the%20BLA%20and%20one%20does%20not%2C%20the%20player%20who%20takes%20the%20money%20is%20statistically%20more%20likely%20to%20make%20it%20to%20the%20majors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20puzzled.%20Why%20would%20that%20be%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20self-selection%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ones%20that%20do%20our%20deals%20really%20care%20about%20making%20it%20and%20will%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20it.%20The%20players%20that%20don't%20do%20it%3F%20They're%20probably%20less%20intelligent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20says%20that%20no%20player%20has%20ever%20signed%20with%20BLA%20because%20they%20were%20desperate%20for%20the%20money.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one's%20forcing%20anybody%20to%20do%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one's%20doing%20this%20out%20of%20need.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20signees%20often%20use%20the%20payments%20to%20purchase%20everything%20from%20personal%20training%20or%20private%20chefs%20to%20a%20new%20mattress.%20%26quot%3BOur%20models%20are%20blind%20to%20your%20background%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20others%20dispute%20that%20assessment.%20The%20primary%20targets%20of%20BLA%20are%20%26quot%3Bindigent%20and%20talented%20players%20from%20Latin%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20baseball%20superagent%20Scott%20Boras%20told%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BFew%20if%20any%20top%20American%20talents%20who%20received%20large%20signing%20bonuses%20would%20ever%20consider%20the%20usurious%20terms.%20The%20idea%20of%20giving%20millions%20in%20lump%20sums%20to%20players%20is%20the%20justification%20of%20candy%20used%20to%20attract%20and%20compel%20players%20to%20give%20up%20huge%20percentages%20of%20their%20careers.%20That%20solely%20benefits%20BLA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20Boras's%20quote%2C%20Schwimer%20wrote%20back%20a%20700-word%20email%20that%20took%20it%20on%20with%20seven%20bullet-pointed%20objections%2C%20including%3A%20%26quot%3B4.%20He%20uses%20the%20term%20'usurious'%20which%20is%20correlated%20to%20loans.%20Words%20have%20actual%20definitions.%20We%20do%20not%20give%20loans%20to%20players%20(no%20one%20thinks%20this).%26quot%3B%20The%20email%20ended%3A%20%26quot%3BAgain%2C%20there%20are%20no%20two%20sides%20to%20BLA.%20Period.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20HBO's%20%26quot%3BReal%20Sports%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efound%20that%20half%20of%20BLA's%20investments%20were%20in%20players%20from%20Latin%20America.%20Yerm%C3%ADn%20Mercedes%2C%20a%20prospect%20highlighted%20in%20the%20segment%2C%20said%20he%20took%20%24165%2C000%20from%20BLA%20for%2015%25%20of%20his%20future%20earnings%20because%20his%20family%20in%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%20was%20relying%20on%20him%20for%20financial%20support.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20big%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20me%20all%20the%20time%20because%20right%20now%20I'm%20the%20head%20of%20my%20family.%20I%20just%20want%20to%20do%20the%20best%20I%20can%20do%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20says%20he%20doesn't%20keep%20track%20of%20players'%20countries%20of%20origin%2C%20so%20he%20couldn't%20offer%20an%20up-to-date%20figure%20on%20who%20it's%20cutting%20deals%20with.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20signed%20over%20100%20American%20players%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20insists%2C%20%26quot%3Bmany%20of%20which%20have%20received%20signing%20bonuses%20in%20the%20millions%20of%20dollars.%26quot%3B%20But%20that%20would%20mean%2C%20by%20Schwimer's%20own%20calculation%2C%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20nearly%20600%20players%20signed%20by%20BLA%20are%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Francisco%20Mej%C3%ADa%2C%20a%20Cleveland%20Indians%20prospect%20who%20accepted%20%24360%2C000%20from%20BLA%20for%2010%25%20of%20his%20future%20earnings%2C%20sued%20the%20fund%20for%20%26quot%3Bunconscionable%20conduct.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20complaint%2C%20he%20claimed%20that%20his%20mother%20was%20sick%20when%20BLA%20approached%20him%20and%20that%20the%20fund%20had%20him%20sign%20a%20draft%20of%20the%20contract%20in%20an%20airport%20without%20an%20interpreter%20present.%20BLA's%20response%20was%20to%20countersue%20Mejia%2C%20who%20wound%20up%20dropping%20his%20lawsuit%20and%20issuing%20a%20public%20apology.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20believe%20Big%20League%20Advance%20has%20ever%20deceived%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gervon%20Dexter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a331b76979d73718233047%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGervon%20Dexter%20is%20suing%20BLA%20for%20signing%20him%20after%20his%20sophomore%20year%20in%20college.%20He%20now%20owes%20the%20fund%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20of%20his%20%246.72%20million%20contract%20with%20the%20Chicago%20Bears.%20%3Cp%3EIcon%20Sportswire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBLA%20has%20more%20recently%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20cutting%20deals%20with%20athletes%20while%20they're%20still%20in%20school.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20defensive%20lineman%20Gervon%20Dexter%20signed%20over%2015%25%20of%20his%20pretax%20future%20earnings%20for%20%24436%2C485%20after%20his%20sophomore%20year%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Dexter%20signed%20a%20four-year%20contract%20for%20%246.72%20million%20with%20the%20Chicago%20Bears%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20of%20which%20he%20would%20have%20to%20hand%20over%20to%20BLA.%20Last%20September%2C%20Dexter%20sued%20BLA%2C%20arguing%20that%20Florida%20law%20allows%20deals%20with%20athletes%20only%20while%20they're%20enrolled%20in%20college%2C%20not%20after%2C%20and%20therefore%20his%20contract%20is%20null%20and%20void.%20An%20initial%20hearing%20will%20be%20held%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20maintains%20that%20he%20has%20always%20followed%20the%20law.%20He%20tells%20me%20he%20tends%20to%20believe%20he%20was%20sued%20by%20Dexter%20and%20Mej%C3%ADa%20because%20advisors%20told%20them%20BLA%20would%20give%20them%20a%20settlement%20to%20avoid%20the%20expense%20and%20the%20reputational%20risk%20of%20going%20to%20court.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20can't%20settle%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20settle%20one%2C%20the%20whole%20company's%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20his%20Wharton%20panel%20begins%2C%20Schwimer%20finds%20me%20in%20the%20atrium%20of%20Huntsman%20Hall.%20He's%20been%20thinking%20about%20why%20all%20the%20media%20coverage%20of%20BLA%20has%20been%20so%20negative.%20%26quot%3BIt%20always%20starts%20with%20a%20writer%20calling%20me%20and%20you%20can%20tell%20wanting%20to%20kill%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%2C%20after%20an%20hour%2C%20they're%20like%2C%20'Actually%2C%20what%20you%20do%20is%20amazing.%20I%20can't%20write%20anything.'%26quot%3B%20Their%20publications%2C%20he%20suggests%2C%20refuse%20to%20run%20the%20stories%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20piss%20off%20powerful%20sports%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20him%2C%20as%20someone%20who%20has%20written%20many%20sports%20stories%2C%20that%20his%20theory%20is%20hard%20to%20square%20with%20my%20experience.%20But%20Schwimer%20continues%20with%20his%20Scwimosohpy.%20Sure%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20and%20the%20home-run%20investments%20like%20Tatis%20are%20newsworthy%2C%20he%20argues.%20But%20why%20not%20write%20about%20all%20the%20guys%20who%20flamed%20out%20and%20got%20to%20keep%20their%20payments%3F%20%26quot%3BI've%20done%20so%20many%20interviews%20just%20like%20this%20one%20where%20you%20go%20back%20to%20your%20editor%20and%20he'll%20be%20like%2C%20'Nah%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20story%20because%20no%20one%20gives%20a%20crap%20about%20the%20people%20that%20don't%20make%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Schwimer%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20what%20it's%20like%20when%20the%20world%20leaves%20you%20for%20dead%20at%2025%2C%2026%20years%20old.%20It's%20brutal.%20And%20nobody%20cares.%20The%20media%20doesn't%20care.%26quot%3B%20He%20pauses.%20%26quot%3BI%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20our%20many%20conversations%2C%20Schwimer%20is%20rarely%20combative%3B%20his%20presentation%20is%20that%20of%20an%20energetic%20star%20of%20a%20high-school%20debate%20team.%20He%20answers%20many%20of%20my%20questions%20with%20questions%20of%20his%20own.%20He%20thinks%20the%20moral%20quandary%20of%20what%20he's%20doing%20is%20a%20fallacy%20that%20can%20be%20disproven%20via%20hypotheticals.%20His%20argument%20that%20it's%20not%20anyone's%20place%20to%20make%20decisions%20on%20behalf%20of%20an%20athlete%20isn't%20especially%20convincing%3A%20Regulatory%20protections%20exist%20for%20a%20reason.%20But%20his%20other%20line%20of%20reasoning%20is%20more%20interesting.%20If%20giving%20up%20%2410%20million%20in%20earnings%20means%20little%20to%20a%20player%20who%20makes%20%24100%20million%2C%20and%20being%20handed%20%24100%2C000%20means%20everything%20to%20a%20broke%20minor%20leaguer%2C%20isn't%20there%20a%20justification%20to%20take%20money%20from%20the%20superstar%20and%20redistribute%20it%20to%20the%20underdog%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps.%20But%20that%2C%20of%20course%2C%20leads%20to%20other%2C%20thornier%20questions.%20Why%20is%20the%20system%20built%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20young%20strivers%20are%20so%20desperate%20for%20quick%20cash%3F%20And%20why%20is%20an%20upstart%20hedge%20fund%20the%20one%20to%20fix%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Wharton%20panel%20on%20college%20sports%20begins%2C%20Schwimer%20is%20in%20his%20element.%20The%20other%20panelists%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sports%20agent%2C%20a%20college%20administrator%2C%20and%20a%20marketing%20executive%20%E2%80%94%20gently%20traipse%20through%20the%20intricacies%20of%20how%20NCAA%20athletes%20can%20be%20compensated%20today.%20Schwimer%20is%20having%20none%20of%20it.%20He%20rails%20against%20corruption%20in%20the%20college-sports%20system%2C%20scoffing%20at%20the%20half%20measures%20that%20keep%20amateur%20athletes%20from%20getting%20the%20money%20they%20deserve%20and%20casting%20himself%20as%20the%20trailblazing%20agent%20of%20disruption.%20So%20what%20if%20he's%20also%20done%20well%20for%20himself%20and%20his%20investors%3F%20He%20explains%2C%20again%20and%20again%2C%20that%20he's%20a%20free-market%20absolutist%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20getting%20kids%20paid.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20believer%20in%20capitalism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20declares.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20believer%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Q%26amp%3BA%20session%2C%20an%20audience%20member%20asks%20about%20the%20way%20businesses%20and%20college%20boosters%20have%20begun%20pooling%20money%20to%20facilitate%20deals%20for%20student%20athletes.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we%20want%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20confused%20attendee%20says.%20%26quot%3BLike%2C%20what%20is%20going%20on%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimer%20points%20to%20the%20college%20administrator%20seated%20beside%20him.%20%26quot%3BHe'll%20give%20you%20the%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20give%20you%20the%20truth!%26quot%3B%20The%20room%20erupts%20in%20laughter%2C%20and%20Schwimer%20smiles.%20For%20today%2C%20at%20least%2C%20the%20B-schoolers%20and%20MBAs%20see%20Schwimer%20just%20as%20he%20sees%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjoseph-bien-kahn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJoseph%20Bien-Kahn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Silverlake.%20He%20covers%20film%2C%20sports%2C%20true%20crime%2C%20and%20oddballs%20for%20GQ%2C%20Vulture%2C%20Sports%20Illustrated%2C%20and%20B