p's%20team%20has%20contained%20%26quot%3Bincomplete%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Binconsistent%26quot%3B%20disclosures%20containing%20multiple%20%26quot%3Berrors.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20she%20describes%20Trump%20and%20his%20businesses%20as%20%26quot%3Bcooperative%26quot%3B%20with%20her%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20buried%20in%20the%20sixth%20footnote%20of%20the%2012-page%20letter%20is%20what%20the%20Daily%20Beast%20indicated%20is%20a%20clue%20that%20Trump%20may%20have%20evaded%20taxes%20on%20%2448%20million%20in%20income%2C%20with%20Jones%20writing%20that%20the%20massive%20sum%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20Trump%20has%20claimed%20for%20years%20that%20he%20owes%20as%20a%20debt%20to%20one%20of%20his%20companies%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0never%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20inquired%20about%20this%20loan%2C%20I%20was%20informed%20that%20there%20are%20no%20loan%20agreements%20that%20memorialize%20the%20loan%2C%20but%20that%20it%20was%20a%20loan%20that%20was%20believed%20to%20be%20between%20Donald%20J.%20Trump%2C%20individually%2C%20and%20Chicago%20Unit%20Acquisition%20for%20%2448%20million%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20in%20recent%20discussions%20with%20the%20Trump%20Organization%2C%20it%20indicated%20that%20it%20has%20determined%20that%20this%20loan%20never%20existed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20that%20it%20would%20be%20removed%20from%20any%20upcoming%20forms%20submitted%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20Government%20Ethics%20(OGE)%20and%20would%20also%20be%20removed%20from%20subsequent%20versions%20of%20MAML%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote%2C%20referring%20to%20corporate%20financial%20statements%20filed%20by%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20and%20Trump%20Organization%20attorney%20Alan%20Garten%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20'pretty%20brazen'%20plot%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGarten%20told%20The%20Daily%20Beast%20an%20%26quot%3Binternal%20loan%26quot%3B%20wherein%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bleant%20money%20to%20the%20entity%20that%20he%20owns%26quot%3B%20does%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20one%20of%20many%20inaccuracies%20contained%20in%20the%20monitor's%20letter%2C%20which%20we%20will%20be%20addressing%20with%20the%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20Garten%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20per%20the%20Daily%20Beast%2C%20as%20recently%20as%20October%2C%20Trump%20has%20claimed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citizensforethics.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FOGE-Certified-Part-2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20disclosures%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20owes%20the%20sum%20to%20his%20company%2C%20Chicago%20Unit%20Acquisition%20LLC%2C%20listing%20his%20debt%20as%20more%20than%20%2450%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discrepancies%2C%20if%20true%2C%20would%20indicate%20that%20the%20disclosures%20Trump%20has%20filed%20with%20the%20federal%20government%20were%20intentionally%20submitted%20with%20inaccuracies%20related%20to%20the%20debt%20equating%20to%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20appear%2C%20assuming%20Judge%20Jones'%20letter%20is%20accurate%2C%20that%20this%20amounts%20to%20tax%20evasion%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20Lobel%2C%20a%20tax%20lawyer%2C%20told%20The%20Daily%20Beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20explains%20why%20the%20Republicans%20have%20been%20so%20intent%20on%20cutting%20the%20IRS's%20budget%2C%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20it%20to%20be%20able%20to%20audit%20transactions%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%2448%20million%20central%20to%20this%20issue%20has%20been%20scrutinized%20before.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20then-candidate%20for%20president%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F05%2F24%2Fbusiness%2Fdealbook%2Fdonald-trump-relationship-bankers.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20New%20Y